-- Bank of Communications Co., Haitong Securities: China Stock-Market Preview
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-23T00:17:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/bank-of-communications-co-haitong-securities-china-stock-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in China trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the last close.  
 The  Shanghai Composite Index , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, gained 2.49, or 0.1 percent, to
2,588.70. The  CSI 300 Index  rose 0.1 percent to 2,783.72.  
 Commodity producers: Export tax rebates on hot-rolled coil,
some cold-rolled coil and galvanized products will be removed,
the Ministry of Finance said in a statement yesterday. The new
policy will also affect some zinc and tin products such as pipes,
foils, plates and rods, the statement said. The new rates will
take effect from July 15, the ministry said.  
 Baoshan Iron & Steel Co.  (600019 CH), the listed unit of
China’s second-biggest steelmaker, added 1 percent to 6.25 yuan.
Hebei Iron & Steel Co. (000709 CH), the listed unit of China’s
biggest steelmaker, fell 0.3 percent to 4.04 yuan. Zhuzhou
Smelter Group Co. (600961 CH), China’s biggest producer of
refined zinc, lost 0.1 percent to 10.37 yuan.  
 Anhui Conch Cement Co.  (600585 CH): China’s biggest cement
maker had its Hong Kong-traded stocks rating cut to “hold”
from “buy” by BNP Paribas analysts Bruce Wang and  Fannie Cui .
The stock dropped 0.4 percent to 17.99 yuan.  
 Bank of Communications Co.  (601328 CH): The lender that’s
part-owned by HSBC Holdings Plc said it completed its rights
issue of 3.8 billion yuan-denominated A shares, raising 17.1
billion yuan ($2.5 billion). The stock gained 3.7 percent to
6.135 yuan.  
 Haitong Securities Co.  (600837 CH): The brokerage said it
will have 763.44 million previously locked-up shares made
tradable on June 29. The stock fell 0.8 percent to 10.63 yuan.  
 -- Zhang Shidong ,  Wang Ying . Editor:  Glenn J. Kalinoski   
